This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as Named Entity Recognition. The paper also mentions the use of clustering semi-supervised features, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of empirical experimentation to effectively combine various types of clustering features, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper focuses on Named Entity Recognition, which is a sub-field of Natural Language Processing, and could also place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
